main event: On June 3, 1965, an object was observed in Dayton, Ohio, which appeared as two lights and moved erratically for about 4 minutes.
interesting points: The object was brighter than stars and disappeared behind trees., Two witnesses included a duty officer and a hunter., The report noted the observation of two 21.33m diameter circles in the area at the time., The object was described as having a white color and erratic motion., It was concluded to be an aircraft.
witness description: a duty officer and a hunter
